{"type":"text","timestamp":1780373424608,"sessionID":"ses_1797a1220ffefMR5XwHZad3Rpm","part":{"id":"prt_e86867e580019yPZDwLRzJxEm6","messageID":"msg_e86866db5001notCKtE673RAZr","sessionID":"ses_1797a1220ffefMR5XwHZad3Rpm","type":"text","text":"The repository confirms the current router does surface slicing and OpenCode language slicing, but the Webflow side still has no equivalent concern sub-slice; I’m checking scenario reports now to quantify whether that gap is measured or only theoretical.","time":{"start":1780373421656,"end":1780373424607},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_094b2f3ea8779e8c016a1e57ad9efc8191a53587147664f125","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780373424636,"sessionID":"ses_1797a1220ffefMR5XwHZad3Rpm","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_cIKJYx5KojzAr1Ae7aqmSeBP","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/references/smart_routing.md","offset":261,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/references/smart_routing.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n261: \n262: - Load only references needed for current intent + surface\n263: - Honor the WEBFLOW implementation trio contract on every WEBFLOW invocation\n264: - Use exact canonical file paths in playbook result YAML (never directory placeholders)\n265: - Load Motion.dev peer resources after the surface decision, not as a substitute\n266: - Cite surface + top-1 intent + loaded resource paths + verification command in your final answer\n267: \n268: ### DON'T\n269: \n270: - Load all of `webflow/` or all of `opencode/` indiscriminately (\"just in case\")\n271: - Treat MOTION_DEV as a surface (it's a peer resource category)\n272: - Load Go/NextJS/React Native resources (those live in the Barter fork)\n273: - Skip the implementation trio for WEBFLOW\n274: - Drop directory placeholders in playbook result YAML\n275: \n276: ---\n277: \n278: ## 10. RELATED RESOURCES\n279: \n280: - [`./stack_detection.md`](./stack_detection.md) — surface detection (WEBFLOW/OPENCODE/UNKNOWN) + OPENCODE language sub-detection\n281: - [`./phase_detection.md`](./phase_detection.md) — Phase 1/2/3 lifecycle and per-phase resource loading\n282: - `SKILL.md` §2 SMART ROUTING — operator-facing summary of this routing contract\n283: - Barter equivalent: `barter/.opencode/skills/sk-code/references/smart_routing.md` (different routing key — git-remote project — but same structural pattern)\n284: \n285: ---\n286: \n287: ## 11. MACHINE-READABLE ROUTER (replay / benchmark source)\n288: \n289: This is the single machine-readable projection of the prose Intent Model (§2) and the per-surface maps (§4 Webflow, §5 Motion.dev, §6 OpenCode). The prose sections above are the human-facing contract; this block is the byte-for-byte source a deterministic router-replay parses. Keep the two in sync: when a map row changes above, update the matching `RESOURCE_MAP` entry here.\n290: \n291: A drift guard (`.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/tests/sk-code-router-sync.vitest.ts`) keeps this block honest: it fails if any path here is missing on disk, if any routable `references/`/`assets/` doc stops being covered, or if an explicit full path named in the prose maps is absent here. Run it standalone with `npx vitest run skill-benchmark/tests/sk-code-router-sync.vitest.ts` from `.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts`.\n292: \n293: This projection is intentionally lossy in two documented ways the flat dictionary cannot express, both enforced by the prose contract and the surface-detection pseudocode in `SKILL.md` §2:\n294: \n295: - **No phase boosts.** The `+5` unambiguous-phase boost from the §2 scoring algorithm is not represented; every keyword carries unit weight here.\n296: - **No doc-only anti-signals.** The `sk-code -2 / sk-doc +3` anti-signals (§2) that route prose-only edits away from this skill are a pre-filter the flat model does not carry.\n297: \n298: ```python\n299: # Always-loaded routing preamble: every code task detects stack, detects phase,\n300: # consults the router, and applies the universal quality baseline before any\n301: # surface-specific resource. These are loaded on every route.\n302: DEFAULT_RESOURCE = [\n303:     \"references/stack_detection.md\",\n304:     \"references/phase_detection.md\",\n305:     \"references/smart_routing.md\",\n306:     \"references/universal/code_quality_standards.md\",\n307: ]\n308: \n309: INTENT_SIGNALS = {\n310:     \"IMPLEMENTATION\":     {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"implement\", \"build\", \"create\", \"feature\", \"component\", \"module\", \"authoring\"]},\n311:     \"CODE_QUALITY\":       {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"lint\", \"format\", \"quality gate\", \"naming\", \"standards\", \"code smell\"]},\n312:     \"DEBUGGING\":          {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"debug\", \"broken\", \"failing\", \"stack trace\", \"console error\", \"regression\"]},\n313:     \"VERIFICATION\":       {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"verify\", \"passing\", \"type-check\", \"alignment drift\", \"completion claim\"]},\n314:     \"TESTING\":            {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"unit test\", \"integration test\", \"coverage\", \"vitest\", \"pytest\", \"shellcheck\"]},\n315:     \"DEPLOYMENT\":         {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"deploy\", \"cdn\", \"wrangler\", \"minify\", \"staging\", \"production release\"]},\n316:     \"PERFORMANCE\":        {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"lighthouse\", \"core web vitals\", \"largest contentful\", \"pagespeed\", \"jank\", \"frame budget\"]},\n317:     \"ANIMATION\":          {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"transition\", \"gsap\", \"lenis\", \"carousel\", \"parallax\"]},\n318:     \"MOTION_DEV\":         {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"motion.dev\", \"motion-dev\", \"animate()\", \"inview\", \"scroll()\", \"cross-stack animation\"]},\n319:     \"FORMS\":              {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"form upload\", \"filepond\", \"field validation\", \"focus trap\"]},\n320:     \"VIDEO\":              {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"hls\", \"adaptive stream\", \"video player\"]},\n321:     \"HOOKS\":              {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"session-prime\", \"user-prompt-submit\", \"pre-tool-use\", \"post-tool-use\"]},\n322:     \"CONFIG\":             {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"jsonc\", \".json\", \".jsonc\", \"descriptor\", \"config schema\"]},\n323:     \"LANGUAGE_STANDARDS\": {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"typescript\", \".ts\", \".tsx\", \"python\", \".py\", \"shell script\", \"bash\", \".sh\", \"commonjs\", \".cjs\", \".mjs\", \"docstring\"]},\n324: }\n325: \n326: RESOURCE_MAP = {\n327:     \"IMPLEMENTATION\": [\n328:         \"references/universal/multi_agent_research.md\",\n329:         \"references/webflow/implementation/implementation_workflows.md\",\n330:         \"references/webflow/implementation/async_patterns.md\",\n331:         \"references/webflow/implementation/observer_patterns.md\",\n332:         \"references/webflow/implementation/security_patterns.md\",\n333:         \"references/webflow/implementation/third_party_integrations.md\",\n334:         \"references/webflow/implementation/webflow_patterns.md\",\n335:         \"references/webflow/shared/dev_workflow.md\",\n336:         \"references/opencode/shared/universal_patterns.md\",\n337:         \"references/opencode/shared/code_organization.md\",\n338:         \"assets/opencode/checklists/agent_authoring.md\",\n339:         \"assets/opencode/checklists/command_authoring.md\",\n340:         \"assets/opencode/checklists/skill_authoring.md\",\n341:         \"assets/opencode/checklists/mcp_server_authoring.md\",\n342:         \"assets/opencode/checklists/spec_folder_authoring.md\",\n343:         \"assets/opencode/recipes/spec_folder_write.md\",\n344:         \"assets/universal/patterns/README.md\",\n345:         \"assets/webflow/integrations/README.md\",\n346:         \"assets/webflow/patterns/README.md\",\n347:         \"assets/webflow/templates/README.md\"\n348:     ],\n349:     \"CODE_QUALITY\": [\n350:         \"references/universal/code_quality_standards.md\",\n351:         \"references/universal/code_style_guide.md\",\n352:         \"references/webflow/shared/cross_language_rules.md\",\n353:         \"references/webflow/shared/enforcement.md\",\n354:         \"assets/opencode/checklists/universal_checklist.md\",\n355:         \"assets/opencode/checklists/javascript_checklist.md\",\n356:         \"assets/opencode/checklists/typescript_checklist.md\",\n357:         \"assets/op