ts/performance_loading_checklist.md\"\n394:     ],\n395:     \"ANIMATION\": [\n396:         \"references/webflow/implementation/animation_workflows.md\",\n397:         \"references/webflow/implementation/swiper_patterns.md\"\n398:     ],\n399:     \"MOTION_DEV\": [\n400:         \"references/motion_dev/quick_start.md\",\n401:         \"references/motion_dev/animate_and_timelines.md\",\n402:         \"references/motion_dev/scroll_and_gestures.md\",\n403:         \"references/motion_dev/integration_patterns.md\",\n404:         \"references/motion_dev/decision_matrix.md\",\n405:         \"assets/motion_dev/install_card.md\",\n406:         \"assets/motion_dev/snippets/README.md\"\n407:     ],\n408:     \"FORMS\": [\n409:         \"references/webflow/implementation/form_upload_workflows.md\",\n410:         \"references/webflow/implementation/focus_management.md\"\n411:     ],\n412:     \"VIDEO\": [\n413:         \"references/webflow/implementation/third_party_integrations.md\"\n414:     ],\n415:     \"HOOKS\": [\n416:         \"references/opencode/shared/hooks.md\"\n417:     ],\n418:     \"CONFIG\": [\n419:         \"references/opencode/config/style_guide.md\",\n420:         \"references/opencode/config/quality_standards.md\",\n421:         \"references/opencode/config/quick_reference.md\",\n422:         \"assets/opencode/checklists/config_checklist.md\"\n423:     ],\n424:     \"LANGUAGE_STANDARDS\": [\n425:         \"references/webflow/css/style_guide.md\",\n426:         \"references/webflow/css/quality_standards.md\",\n427:         \"references/webflow/css/quick_reference.md\",\n428:         \"references/webflow/css/patterns.md\",\n429:         \"references/webflow/html/style_guide.md\",\n430:         \"references/webflow/html/quality_standards.md\",\n431:         \"references/webflow/javascript/style_guide.md\",\n432:         \"references/webflow/javascript/quality_standards.md\",\n433:         \"references/webflow/javascript/quick_reference.md\",\n434:         \"references/opencode/javascript/style_guide.md\",\n435:         \"references/opencode/javascript/quality_standards.md\",\n436:         \"references/opencode/javascript/quick_reference.md\",\n437:         \"references/opencode/typescript/style_guide.md\",\n438:         \"references/opencode/typescript/quality_standards.md\",\n439:         \"references/opencode/typescript/quick_reference.md\",\n440:         \"references/opencode/python/style_guide.md\",\n441:         \"references/opencode/python/quality_standards.md\",\n442:         \"references/opencode/python/quick_reference.md\",\n443:         \"references/opencode/shell/style_guide.md\",\n444:         \"references/opencode/shell/quality_standards.md\",\n445:         \"references/opencode/shell/quick_reference.md\"\n446:     ],\n447: }\n448: ```\n449: \n450: ### Surface-aware loading (route-time)\n451: \n452: The router does NOT load the whole matched-intent union. After surface detection (§1, `stack_detection.md`), a route loads:\n453: \n454: - the always-loaded `DEFAULT_RESOURCE` preamble (stack/phase detection, the router, the universal quality baseline), plus\n455: - the surface-agnostic `references/universal/*` tier, plus\n456: - only the **detected surface's** slice (`references/<surface>/*`) for the matched intents, plus\n457: - the Motion.dev overlay (`references/motion_dev/*`) when a `MOTION_DEV` intent fires.\n458: \n459: It does not load the other surface's resources, and it defers `assets/*` (checklists, recipes, templates) to on-demand rather than the first slice. Within OpenCode it slices once more by the **detected language** (§1 sub-detection): a TypeScript task loads `references/opencode/typescript/*` plus the language-agnostic `references/opencode/shared/*`, not the Python, shell, config, or JavaScript folders. Webflow has no language sub-slice — a frontend task legitimately spans CSS, HTML, and JavaScript together. A task that genuinely spans both surfaces (mixed `.opencode/` and Webflow markers) keeps both surface slices; an `UNKNOWN` surface falls back to the preamble plus the universal tier and the Motion overlay only. This is what stops a routine single-surface task from pulling the full cross-surface set. The deterministic router-replay enforces the same rule, so the benchmark measures it.\n\n(End of file - total 459 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\n- Load only references needed for current intent + surface\n- Honor the WEBFLOW implementation trio contract on every WEBFLOW invocation\n- Use exact canonical file paths in playbook result YAML (never directory placeholders)\n- Load Motion.dev peer resources after the surface decision, not as a substitute\n- Cite surface + top-1 intent + loaded resource paths + verification command in your final answer\n\n### DON'T\n\n- Load all of `webflow/` or all of `opencode/` indiscriminately (\"just in case\")\n- Treat MOTION_DEV as a surface (it's a peer resource category)\n- Load Go/NextJS/React Native resources (those live in the Barter fork)\n- Skip the implementation trio for WEBFLOW\n- Drop directory placeholders in playbook result YAML\n\n---\n\n## 10. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n- [`./stack_detection.md`](./stack_detection.md) — surface detection (WEBFLOW/OPENCODE/UNKNOWN) + OPENCODE language sub-detection","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/references/smart_routing.md","time":{"start":1780373424629,"end":1780373424635}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_094b2f3ea8779e8c016a1e57b0925881918be9bba3eacd1223"}},"id":"prt_e868689e0001G7D6H3422LK4hA","sessionID":"ses_1797a1220ffefMR5XwHZad3Rpm","messageID":"msg_e86866db5001notCKtE673RAZr"}}
