{"type":"text","timestamp":1780373471973,"sessionID":"ses_1797a1220ffefMR5XwHZad3Rpm","part":{"id":"prt_e868732d1001Z918ilC4eLVVbK","messageID":"msg_e8687227c0018qq7z4OovgrA1a","sessionID":"ses_1797a1220ffefMR5XwHZad3Rpm","type":"text","text":"The playbook loader confirms expected assets are captured but separate from expected resources; that means concern-slicing claims must distinguish scored D3/D2 from behavior-relevant assets.","time":{"start":1780373467857,"end":1780373471969},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0d808f4d72e41876016a1e57dbd3988191bdebd85ce2c15421","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780373472069,"sessionID":"ses_1797a1220ffefMR5XwHZad3Rpm","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_k4egwYcgNX533fxy05KkGRfT","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/benchmark/README.md","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/benchmark/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"sk-code Skill-Benchmark Artifacts\"\n3: description: \"Benchmark inputs and reports for sk-code, scored by the deep-improvement Lane C harness in router and live modes.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"sk-code benchmark\"\n6:   - \"skill-benchmark artifacts\"\n7:   - \"sk-code routing benchmark\"\n8: ---\n9: \n10: # sk-code Skill-Benchmark Artifacts\n11: \n12: > Reports and inputs for benchmarking how well `sk-code` is routed, discovered, and used in practice, kept beside the skill they measure.\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n17: \n18: The deep-improvement Lane C harness benchmarks `sk-code` against its own `manual_testing_playbook` scenarios across five dimensions (D1 routing, D2 discovery, D3 efficiency, D4 usefulness, D5 connectivity). This folder holds the run inputs and the dual reports each run writes.\n19: \n20: Two trace modes score the same playbook corpus:\n21: \n22: - **router** is deterministic and offline. It replays the machine-readable router in `sk-code/references/smart_routing.md`. This is the CI gate.\n23: - **live** dispatches each scenario through `cli-opencode` to a real model and grades the model's stated routing plus observed activation. This is the operator default for a true routing verdict.\n24: \n25: ### Key Statistics\n26: \n27: | Metric | Value |\n28: |---|---|\n29: | Corpus | sk-code `manual_testing_playbook` (24 scenarios: 15 routing, 2 advisor, 7 browser) |\n30: | Trace modes | router (deterministic CI gate), live (real dispatch) |\n31: | Latest router verdict | FAIL, aggregate 40 |\n32: | Latest live verdict | CONDITIONAL, aggregate 71 |\n33: | D4 usefulness (approximate) | about 49 |\n34: \n35: ### How This Compares\n36: \n37: | Tool | Checks | Use When |\n38: |---|---|---|\n39: | This benchmark | Whether the skill is routed, discovered, and useful in practice | Measuring real routing quality |\n40: | `validate.sh` | Document shape and required sections | Checking spec-folder structure |\n41: | `manual_testing_playbook` | Described behavior per scenario | Authoring or hand-running scenarios |\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: ## 2. QUICK START\n46: \n47: Run from the repository root.\n48: \n49: Router mode (deterministic, no network):\n50: \n51: ```bash\n52: node .opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs \\\n53:   --mode=skill-benchmark --skill=sk-code \\\n54:   --outputs-dir=.opencode/skills/sk-code/benchmark/router-final \\\n55:   --trace-mode=router\n56: ```\n57: \n58: Live mode (dispatches through cli-opencode, needs a configured provider):\n59: \n60: ```bash\n61: SKILL_BENCH_OPENCODE_MODEL=openai/gpt-5.5-fast SKILL_BENCH_OPENCODE_VARIANT=high \\\n62: node .opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs \\\n63:   --mode=skill-benchmark --skill=sk-code \\\n64:   --outputs-dir=.opencode/skills/sk-code/benchmark/live-final \\\n65:   --trace-mode=live --advisor-mode=python \\\n66:   --scenarios=SD-001,LS-001,CS-001,RD-002,MR-001\n67: ```\n68: \n69: Expected result: a `verdict=` line on stdout plus `skill-benchmark-report.json` and `skill-benchmark-report.md` in the outputs dir.\n70: \n71: ---\n72: \n73: ## 3. STRUCTURE\n74: \n75: ```text\n76: benchmark/\n77: +-- router-final/      # Current deterministic run (router mode)\n78: +-- live-final/        # Current live run (cli-opencode) + d4-ablation.json\n79: +-- baseline/          # Frozen pre-optimization snapshot, do not regenerate\n80: +-- after/ full/ live/ # Earlier development runs, superseded by the -final pair\n81: `-- fixtures/sk-code/   # Legacy synthetic fixtures, superseded by the playbook corpus\n82: ```\n83: \n84: | Path | Purpose |\n85: |---|---|\n86: | `router-final/` | Latest router-mode report (real-gold scoring, the CI gate) |\n87: | `live-final/` | Latest live-mode report plus `d4-ablation.json` (skill-on vs skill-off usefulness) |\n88: | `baseline/` | First sk-code run, kept as a before-snapshot, not reproducible |\n89: | `fixtures/sk-code/` | Two legacy fixtures, no longer the default corpus |\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ## 4. READING THE REPORTS\n94: \n95: Each run writes a matched pair:\n96: \n97: | File | Content |\n98: |---|---|\n99: | `skill-benchmark-report.json` | Machine report: verdict, D1 to D5, funnel, ranked bottlenecks, scenario rows |\n100: | `skill-benchmark-report.md` | The same report rendered for reading, generated from the JSON to avoid drift |\n101: | `d4-ablation.json` | Usefulness deltas per scenario (skill-on score, skill-off score), stamped approximate |\n102: \n103: Start with the `.md` file for the verdict and the ranked bottlenecks. Open the `.json` file for per-scenario detail.\n104: \n105: ---\n106: \n107: ## 5. TROUBLESHOOTING\n108: \n109: | What you see | Cause | Fix |\n110: |---|---|---|\n111: | Live dispatch returns null after about 4 minutes | `xhigh` reasoning variant is too slow per dispatch | Set `SKILL_BENCH_OPENCODE_VARIANT=high` |\n112: | `provider/model not found` or 401 in live mode | The provider is not configured | Run `opencode providers list`, then log in to the provider you name in `SKILL_BENCH_OPENCODE_MODEL` |\n113: | Browser scenarios skip with `SKIP-NO-BROWSER` | `bdg` (Chrome) is unavailable | Install `bdg`, or accept the honest skip for non-Chrome legs |\n114: | Router mode reports orphan references | A routable doc is not reachable from the router | Add it to `RESOURCE_MAP` or the always-loaded default in `smart_routing.md` |\n115: \n116: ---\n117: \n118: ## 6. RELATED RESOURCES\n119: \n120: ### Related Skills\n\n(Showing lines 1-120 of 132. Use offset=121 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"sk-code Skill-Benchmark Artifacts\"\ndescription: \"Benchmark inputs and reports for sk-code, scored by the deep-improvement Lane C harness in router and live modes.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"sk-code benchmark\"\n  - \"skill-benchmark artifacts\"\n  - \"sk-code routing benchmark\"\n---\n\n# sk-code Skill-Benchmark Artifacts\n\n> Reports and inputs for benchmarking how well `sk-code` is routed, discovered, and used in practice, kept beside the skill they measure.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThe deep-improvement Lane C harness benchmarks `sk-code` against its own `manual_testing_playbook` scenarios across five dimensions (D1 routing, D2 discovery, D3 efficiency, D4 usefulness, D5 connectivity). This folder holds the run inputs and the dual reports each run writes.\n\nTwo trace modes score the same playbook corpus:","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/benchmark/README.md","time":{"start":1780373472051,"end":1780373472063}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d808f4d72e41876016a1e57dfedc881918bad387569c34c4b"}},"id":"prt_e8687432e001WkaC1rf06oMpw3","sessionID":"ses_1797a1220ffefMR5XwHZad3Rpm","messageID":"msg_e8687227c0018qq7z4OovgrA1a"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780373472069,"sessionID":"ses_1797a1220ffefMR5XwHZad3Rpm","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_0WaNeDJJpOmElwjybVdv9iBB","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/02--language-sub-detection/005-opencode-python.md","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/02--language-sub-detection/005-opencode-python.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"LS-002: OPENCODE Python Sub-Detection\"\n3: description: \"Verify that within OPENCODE surface, Python file extensions trigger loading of python/* references (not typescript, shell, or config).\"\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # LS-002: OPENCODE Python Sub-Detection\n7: \n8: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n9: \n10: Verify language sub-detection for `.py` files within OPENCODE surface. The Python ref set MUST load; TypeScript/Shell/Config sets MUST NOT.\n11: \n12: Sub-detection rules defined in SKILL.md lines 78-90.\n13: \n14: ## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n15: \n16: **Realistic user request**: Add a `--json-output` flag to the skill advisor CLI for machine-readable results.\n17: \n18: **Exact prompt**:\n19: ```\n20: Update the skill_advisor.py argparse block at .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py to add a --json-output flag that emits results as JSON.\n21: ```\n22: \n23: **Expected detection**:\n24: - Surface: `OPENCODE`\n25: - Sub-language: `PYTHON` (target file `.py`, also Python-specific signal: `argparse`)\n26: \n27: **Expected references loaded**:\n28: - `references/opencode/python/style_guide.md`\n29: - `references/opencode/python/quality_standards.md`\n30: - `references/opencode/python/quick_reference.md`\n31: - `references/opencode/shared/code_organization.md`\n32: - `references/opencode/shared/universal_patterns.md`\n33: \n34: **Expected assets loaded**:\n35: - `assets/opencode/checklists/python_checklist.md`\n36: - `assets/opencode/checklists/universal_checklist.md`\n37: \n38: **Expected NOT loaded**: any of `references/opencode/{typescript,shell,config}/*`.\n39: \n40: ## 3. TEST EXECUTION\n41: \n42: ### Preconditions\n43: \n44: 1. Target file exists: `bash: test -f .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py`\n45: 2. Python sub-language reference set intact: 3 files under `references/opencode/python/`.\n46: \n47: ### Exact Command Sequence\n48: \n49: 1. Invoke sk-code with the prompt.\n50: 2. Capture loaded refs to `/tmp/skc-LS002-loaded-refs.txt`.\n51: 3. Verify: 3 python/* + 2 shared/* refs loaded; 0 typescript/shell/config refs.\n52: \n53: ### Pass/Fail Criteria\n54: \n55: - **PASS** iff: 3 python/* refs + 2 shared/* refs loaded AND 0 other-sub-language refs.\n56: - **FAIL** iff: any typescript/shell/config ref leaks, OR fewer than 3 python/* refs loaded.\n57: \n58: ### Failure Triage\n59: \n60: 1. If a typescript/* ref leaks: the extension detector is mis-firing on the `.py` extension.\n61: 2. If python signals not detected: verify `argparse`, `pytest`, `def `, docstring patterns in SKILL.md sub-detection table.\n62: \n63: ## 4. SOURCE FILES\n64: \n65: - `.opencode/skills/sk-code/SKILL.md` (sub-detection table).\n66: - `.opencode/skills/sk-code/references/opencode/python/{style_guide,quality_standards,quick_reference}.md`.\n67: \n68: ## 5. SOURCE METADATA\n69: \n70: - **Created**: 2026-05-04\n71: - **Critical path**: No\n72: - **Destructive**: No\n73: - **Concurrent-safe**: Yes\n74: - **Last validated**: pending first manual run\n\n(End of file - total 74 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"LS-002: OPENCODE Python Sub-Detection\"\ndescription: \"Verify that within OPENCODE surface, Python file extensions trigger loading of python/* references (not typescript, shell, or config).\"\n---\n\n# LS-002: OPENCODE Python Sub-Detection\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nVerify language sub-detection for `.py` files within OPENCODE surface. The Python ref set MUST load; TypeScript/Shell/Config sets MUST NOT.\n\nSub-detection rules defined in SKILL.md lines 78-90.\n\n## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n\n**Realistic user request**: Add a `--json-output` flag to the skill advisor CLI for machine-readable results.\n\n**Exact prompt**:\n```\nUpdate the skill_advisor.py argparse block at .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py to add a --json-output flag that emits results as JSON.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/02--language-sub-detection/005-opencode-python.md","time":{"start":1780373472032,"end":1780373472065}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d808f4d72e41876016a1e57dfedb08191a649659377c5ba14"}},"id":"prt_e868742e6001VvX93CflIVy8KM","sessionID":"ses_1797a1220ffefMR5XwHZad3Rpm","messageID":"msg_e8687227c0018qq7z4OovgrA1a"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780373472069,"sessionID":"ses_1797a1220ffefMR5XwHZad3Rpm","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_agP1kAQdMYLkTUVQBsKglzen","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/02--language-sub-detection/004-opencode-typescript.md","offset":1,"limit":115},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/02--language-sub-detection/004-opencode-typescript.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"LS-001: OPENCODE TypeScript Sub-Detection\"\n3: description: \"Verify that within OPENCODE surface, TypeScript file extensions trigger loading of typescript/* references (not python, shell, or config).\"\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # LS-001: OPENCODE TypeScript Sub-Detection\n7: \n8: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n9: \n10: This scenario verifies the language sub-detection layer within OPENCODE. When the target file extension is `.ts`, `.tsx`, `.mts`, or `.d.ts`, sk-code MUST load the `references/opencode/typescript/*` set and corresponding `assets/opencode/checklists/typescript_checklist.md`, while excluding python, shell, and config sub-language references.\n11: \n12: Sub-detection rules are defined in SKILL.md lines 78-90 and `references/stack_detection.md:50-62`.\n13: \n14: ## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n15: \n16: **Realistic user request**: A maintainer wants to harden the executor-config parser to throw early when an invalid model is supplied for cli-codex.\n17: \n18: **Exact prompt**:\n19: ```\n20: Refactor the parseExecutorConfig function in .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts to throw on missing model when type is cli-codex.\n21: ```\n22: \n23: **Expected detection**:\n24: - Surface: `OPENCODE`\n25: - Sub-language: `TYPESCRIPT` (target file `.ts`)\n26: \n27: **Expected references loaded** (must be EXACTLY this set, no more, no less from the language tier):\n28: - `references/opencode/typescript/style_guide.md`\n29: - `references/opencode/typescript/quality_standards.md`\n30: - `references/opencode/typescript/quick_reference.md`\n31: - `references/opencode/shared/code_organization.md`\n32: - `references/opencode/shared/universal_patterns.md`\n33: \n34: **Expected assets loaded**:\n35: - `assets/opencode/checklists/typescript_checklist.md`\n36: - `assets/opencode/checklists/universal_checklist.md`\n37: \n38: **Expected NOT loaded**: any of `references/opencode/{python,shell,config}/*`, any of `assets/opencode/checklists/{python,shell,config}_checklist.md`.\n39: \n40: ## 3. TEST EXECUTION\n41: \n42: ### Preconditions\n43: \n44: 1. Target file exists: `bash: test -f .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`\n45: 2. TypeScript sub-language reference set intact: `bash: ls .opencode/skills/sk-code/references/opencode/typescript/ | sort` returns exactly `quality_standards.md style_guide.md quick_reference.md` (in some sort order).\n46: \n47: ### Exact Command Sequence\n48: \n49: 1. **Invoke sk-code** with the prompt.\n50: 2. **Capture loaded refs** to `/tmp/skc-LS001-loaded-refs.txt`.\n51: 3. **Verify**: 3 typescript/* + 2 shared/* refs loaded; 0 python/shell/config refs loaded.\n52: \n53: ### Pass/Fail Criteria\n54: \n55: - **PASS** iff: exactly 3 typescript/* refs + 2 shared/* refs in load set AND 0 other-sub-language refs.\n56: - **FAIL** iff: any python/shell/config sub-language ref is loaded, OR fewer than 3 typescript/* refs loaded.\n57: \n58: ### Failure Triage\n59: \n60: 1. If a python/shell/config ref leaks: verify the file extension parsing in SKILL.md sub-detection table.\n61: 2. If quick_reference.md is missing: check whether the quick-reference always-load rule in `resource_loading.md` is intact.\n62: \n63: ## 4. SOURCE FILES\n64: \n65: - `.opencode/skills/sk-code/SKILL.md` (lines 78-90 — sub-detection table).\n66: - `.opencode/skills/sk-code/references/stack_detection.md` (lines 50-62).\n67: - `.opencode/skills/sk-code/references/opencode/typescript/{style_guide,quality_standards,quick_reference}.md`.\n68: \n69: ## 5. SOURCE METADATA\n70: \n71: - **Created**: 2026-05-04\n72: - **Critical path**: No\n73: - **Destructive**: No\n74: - **Concurrent-safe**: Yes\n75: - **Last validated**: pending first manual run\n\n(End of file - total 75 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"LS-001: OPENCODE TypeScript Sub-Detection\"\ndescription: \"Verify that within OPENCODE surface, TypeScript file extensions trigger loading of typescript/* references (not python, shell, or config).\"\n---\n\n# LS-001: OPENCODE TypeScript Sub-Detection\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThis scenario verifies the language sub-detection layer within OPENCODE. When the target file extension is `.ts`, `.tsx`, `.mts`, or `.d.ts`, sk-code MUST load the `references/opencode/typescript/*` set and corresponding `assets/opencode/checklists/typescript_checklist.md`, while excluding python, shell, and config sub-language references.\n\nSub-detection rules are defined in SKILL.md lines 78-90 and `references/stack_detection.md:50-62`.\n\n## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n\n**Realistic user request**: A maintainer wants to harden the executor-config parser to throw early when an invalid model is supplied for cli-codex.\n\n**Exact prompt**:\n```\nRefactor the parseExecutorConfig function in .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts to throw on missing model when type is cli-codex.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/02--language-sub-detection/004-opencode-typescript.md","time":{"start":1780373472043,"end":1780373472066}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d808f4d72e41876016a1e57dfedc0819183b16a05bffabac6"}},"id":"prt_e86874325001XL33Dv83vScZWC","sessionID":"ses_1797a1220ffefMR5XwHZad3Rpm","messageID":"msg_e8687227c0018qq7z4OovgrA1a"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780373472069,"sessionID":"ses_1797a1220ffefMR5XwHZad3Rpm","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_qIU3uSsiAfS9JLQdglm9VEij","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/d5-connectivity.cjs","offset":1,"limit":160},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/d5-connectivity.cjs</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: #!/usr/bin/env node\n2: 'use strict';\n3: \n4: /**\n5:  * d5-connectivity.cjs — static structural scan, the D5 hard gate.\n6:  *\n7:  * Runs BEFORE any dispatch and caps the verdict regardless of weighted score.\n8:  * Catches the failure class that makes a skill structurally unusable: a\n9:  * RESOURCE_MAP path that does not exist (dead route), a RESOURCE_MAP key absent\n10:  * from INTENT_SIGNALS (dead intent key), a routed path escaping the skill root,\n11:  * and references present on disk but never reachable from any RESOURCE_MAP entry\n12:  * (orphans — reported, not gated). A router that cannot be parsed at all is the\n13:  * strongest gate failure.\n14:  */\n15: \n16: const fs = require('fs');\n17: const path = require('path');\n18: const { parseRouter } = require('./router-replay.cjs');\n19: \n20: function listMarkdownRefs(skillRoot) {\n21:   const out = [];\n22:   for (const dir of ['references', 'assets']) {\n23:     const base = path.join(skillRoot, dir);\n24:     if (!fs.existsSync(base)) continue;\n25:     const stack = [base];\n26:     while (stack.length) {\n27:       const cur = stack.pop();\n28:       for (const entry of fs.readdirSync(cur, { withFileTypes: true })) {\n29:         const full = path.join(cur, entry.name);\n30:         if (entry.isDirectory()) stack.push(full);\n31:         else if (entry.isFile() && /\\.md$/.test(entry.name)) out.push(path.relative(skillRoot, full));\n32:       }\n33:     }\n34:   }\n35:   return out;\n36: }\n37: \n38: /**\n39:  * @returns {{ score:number, gateFailed:boolean, findings:Array,\n40:  *   deadResourcePaths:string[], deadIntentKeys:string[], orphanReferences:string[],\n41:  *   pathEscapes:string[], routerParseable:boolean }}\n42:  */\n43: function scanConnectivity({ skillRoot }) {\n44:   const findings = [];\n45:   const skillMdPath = path.join(skillRoot, 'SKILL.md');\n46:   if (!fs.existsSync(skillMdPath)) {\n47:     // Score mirrors the normal penalty path (100 - one P0 of 40 = 60) so a\n48:     // score-comparison consumer sees the same number for the same one-P0\n49:     // condition; gateFailed is the authoritative verdict signal either way.\n50:     return {\n51:       score: 60, gateFailed: true, routerParseable: false,\n52:       deadResourcePaths: [], deadIntentKeys: [], orphanReferences: [], pathEscapes: [],\n53:       findings: [{ class: 'missing_skill_md', severity: 'P0', detail: 'SKILL.md not found' }],\n54:     };\n55:   }\n56:   const router = parseRouter(fs.readFileSync(skillMdPath, 'utf8'), skillRoot);\n57:   const intentKeys = new Set(Object.keys(router.intentSignals));\n58:   const deadResourcePaths = [];\n59:   const deadIntentKeys = [];\n60:   const pathEscapes = [];\n61:   const routedRefs = new Set();\n62:   // Always-loaded default resources are reachable on every route, so they count\n63:   // as covered (not orphans) even when no intent maps to them.\n64:   for (const r of router.defaultResource || []) routedRefs.add(r);\n65: \n66:   for (const [intent, resources] of Object.entries(router.resourceMap)) {\n67:     if (!intentKeys.has(intent)) {\n68:       deadIntentKeys.push(intent);\n69:       findings.push({ class: 'dead_intent_key', severity: 'P1', locus: `RESOURCE_MAP.${intent}`, detail: `${intent} has no INTENT_SIGNALS entry` });\n70:     }\n71:     for (const r of resources) {\n72:       routedRefs.add(r);\n73:       const root = path.resolve(skillRoot);\n74:       const resolved = path.resolve(skillRoot, r);\n75:       // Separator-bounded containment: a bare startsWith(root) would let a\n76:       // sibling like `<root>-evil/...` slip through as \"inside\" the skill root.\n77:       if (resolved !== root && !resolved.startsWith(root + path.sep)) {\n78:         pathEscapes.push(r);\n79:         findings.push({ class: 'path_escape', severity: 'P0', locus: r, detail: `${r} resolves outside skill root` });\n80:       } else if (!fs.existsSync(resolved)) {\n81:         deadResourcePaths.push(r);\n82:         findings.push({ class: 'dead_resource_path', severity: 'P0', locus: r, detail: `routed path ${r} does not exist` });\n83:       }\n84:     }\n85:   }\n86: \n87:   const orphanReferences = listMarkdownRefs(skillRoot).filter((ref) => !routedRefs.has(ref));\n88:   for (const orphan of orphanReferences) {\n89:     findings.push({ class: 'orphan_reference', severity: 'P2', locus: orphan, detail: `${orphan} is not reachable from any RESOURCE_MAP intent` });\n90:   }\n91: \n92:   // Hard gate: any P0 (dead path / escape / unparseable). Dead intent keys (P1)\n93:   // and orphans (P2) lower the score but do not gate by themselves.\n94:   const p0 = findings.filter((f) => f.severity === 'P0').length;\n95:   const gateFailed = p0 > 0 || !router.parseable;\n96:   if (!router.parseable) {\n97:     findings.push({ class: 'router_unparseable', severity: 'P0', detail: 'INTENT_SIGNALS / RESOURCE_MAP could not be parsed from SKILL.md' });\n98:   }\n99:   // Score: start at 100, subtract per finding by severity, floor 0.\n100:   const penalty = findings.reduce((acc, f) => acc + ({ P0: 40, P1: 12, P2: 3 }[f.severity] || 0), 0);\n101:   const score = Math.max(0, 100 - penalty);\n102: \n103:   return { score, gateFailed, routerParseable: router.parseable, deadResourcePaths, deadIntentKeys, orphanReferences, pathEscapes, findings };\n104: }\n105: \n106: module.exports = { scanConnectivity, listMarkdownRefs };\n107: \n108: if (require.main === module) {\n109:   const args = require('./_args.cjs').parse(process.argv.slice(2));\n110:   if (!args.skill) {\n111:     process.stderr.write('usage: d5-connectivity.cjs --skill <skill-root>\\n');\n112:     process.exit(2);\n113:   }\n114:   const res = scanConnectivity({ skillRoot: args.skill });\n115:   process.stdout.write(JSON.stringify(res, null, 2) + '\\n');\n116:   process.exit(res.gateFailed ? 1 : 0);\n117: }\n\n(End of file - total 117 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n'use strict';\n\n/**\n * d5-connectivity.cjs — static structural scan, the D5 hard gate.\n *\n * Runs BEFORE any dispatch and caps the verdict regardless of weighted score.\n * Catches the failure class that makes a skill structurally unusable: a\n * RESOURCE_MAP path that does not exist (dead route), a RESOURCE_MAP key absent\n * from INTENT_SIGNALS (dead intent key), a routed path escaping the skill root,\n * and references present on disk but never reachable from any RESOURCE_MAP entry\n * (orphans — reported, not gated). A router that cannot be parsed at all is the\n * strongest gate failure.\n */\n\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst path = require('path');\nconst { parseRouter } = require('./router-replay.cjs');\n\nfunction listMarkdownRefs(skillRoot) {","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/d5-connectivity.cjs","time":{"start":1780373472056,"end":1780373472068}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d808f4d72e41876016a1e57dfedd0819197e8b7d40bfd6740"}},"id":"prt_e86874336001pD01GAu00WU3DM","sessionID":"ses_1797a1220ffefMR5XwHZad3Rpm","messageID":"msg_e8687227c0018qq7z4OovgrA1a"}}
