{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780373523656,"sessionID":"ses_1797a1220ffefMR5XwHZad3Rpm","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_KTtCZyppfSi4MSKOY0eTAjoa","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/07--cross-stack-routing/023-cwv-gates-animation-heavy.md","offset":1,"limit":95},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/07--cross-stack-routing/023-cwv-gates-animation-heavy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"CS-006: Animation-Heavy Core Web Vitals Gates\"\n3: description: \"Verify animation-heavy Webflow performance prompts load both Motion.dev performance guidance and Webflow CWV remediation guidance.\"\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # CS-006: Animation-Heavy Core Web Vitals Gates\n7: \n8: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n9: \n10: This scenario verifies dual performance loading. A Webflow page with Motion.dev-heavy animation needs Webflow Core Web Vitals remediation plus Motion.dev animation-performance pitfalls. Loading only one side loses either platform constraints or API-specific risks.\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n15: \n16: **Realistic user prompt**:\n17: ```text\n18: Our Webflow landing page in src/2_javascript/hero.js uses motion.dev for scroll reveals and hover cards. LCP and INP regressed. Which sk-code references would you load before advising fixes?\n19: ```\n20: \n21: **Expected detection markers** (verbatim from `references/stack_detection.md`):\n22: ```bash\n23: # 2. WEBFLOW\n24: [ -d \"src/2_javascript\" ]\n25: ls *.webflow.js 2>/dev/null | head -1\n26: grep -lq \"Webflow\\.push\\|--vw-\" src/**/*.{js,css,html} 2>/dev/null\n27: grep -lqE \"window\\.Motion|window\\.gsap|gsap\\.(to|from|set|timeline|registerPlugin)|new Lenis|new Hls|new Swiper|FilePond\" \\\n28:   src/**/*.{js,mjs,ts,html} *.{js,mjs,ts,html} 2>/dev/null\n29: [ -f \"wrangler.toml\" ]\n30: ```\n31: \n32: **Expected surface**: `WEBFLOW`\n33: \n34: **Expected references loaded** (exact relative paths under `.opencode/skills/sk-code/`):\n35: - `references/stack_detection.md`\n36: - `references/smart_routing.md`\n37: - `references/smart_routing.md`\n38: - `references/webflow/performance/cwv_remediation.md`\n39: - `references/webflow/performance/interaction_gated_loading.md`\n40: - `references/webflow/performance/resource_loading.md`\n41: - `references/webflow/verification/performance_checklist.md`\n42: - `references/motion_dev/performance_and_pitfalls.md`\n43: - `references/motion_dev/decision_matrix.md`\n44: \n45: **Expected assets loaded**:\n46: - `assets/webflow/checklists/performance_loading_checklist.md`\n47: - `assets/webflow/patterns/performance_patterns.js`\n48: \n49: **Expected agent dispatch**: none.\n50: \n51: **Pass/fail criteria with binary grading**:\n52: - **PASS** iff surface is `WEBFLOW` and the load set includes both `references/motion_dev/performance_and_pitfalls.md` and `references/webflow/performance/cwv_remediation.md`.\n53: - **FAIL** iff either required performance reference is missing, surface is not `WEBFLOW`, or an agent is dispatched.\n54: \n55: **Failure triage**:\n56: 1. If Webflow performance refs are missing, inspect the `PERFORMANCE` map in `references/smart_routing.md`.\n57: 2. If Motion performance refs are missing, inspect the `MOTION_DEV` map in the same file.\n58: 3. If surface is wrong, verify `src/2_javascript/hero.js` is present in the prompt.\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ## 3. TEST EXECUTION\n63: \n64: Run this scenario through the Phase 005 universal prompt using `SCENARIO_ID=CS-006`.\n65: \n66: Evidence files:\n67: - `/tmp/skc-CS-006-<cli>.txt`\n68: - `<spec-folder><cli>.yaml`\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: ## 4. SOURCE FILES\n73: \n74: - `.opencode/skills/sk-code/references/webflow/performance/cwv_remediation.md` - Required Webflow CWV reference.\n75: - `.opencode/skills/sk-code/references/motion_dev/performance_and_pitfalls.md` - Required Motion performance reference.\n76: - `.opencode/skills/sk-code/assets/webflow/checklists/performance_loading_checklist.md` - Expected asset.\n77: \n78: ---\n79: \n80: ## 5. SOURCE METADATA\n81: \n82: - **Created**: 2026-05-05\n83: - **Critical path**: No\n84: - **Destructive**: No\n85: - **Sandbox**: read-only routing analysis\n86: - **Concurrent-safe**: Yes\n87: - **Last validated**: pending Phase D matrix\n\n(End of file - total 87 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"CS-006: Animation-Heavy Core Web Vitals Gates\"\ndescription: \"Verify animation-heavy Webflow performance prompts load both Motion.dev performance guidance and Webflow CWV remediation guidance.\"\n---\n\n# CS-006: Animation-Heavy Core Web Vitals Gates\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThis scenario verifies dual performance loading. A Webflow page with Motion.dev-heavy animation needs Webflow Core Web Vitals remediation plus Motion.dev animation-performance pitfalls. Loading only one side loses either platform constraints or API-specific risks.\n\n---\n\n## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n\n**Realistic user prompt**:\n```text\nOur Webflow landing page in src/2_javascript/hero.js uses motion.dev for scroll reveals and hover cards. LCP and INP regressed. Which sk-code references would you load before advising fixes?\n```\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/07--cross-stack-routing/023-cwv-gates-animation-heavy.md","time":{"start":1780373523629,"end":1780373523653}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b8cddaa3b01415f016a1e581385c481919eaf4b09af029111"}},"id":"prt_e86880c8f001upTMQYpjlQFOLU","sessionID":"ses_1797a1220ffefMR5XwHZad3Rpm","messageID":"msg_e8687bcc4001cmmNK3o2tn488b"}}
