: \n32: **Expected surface**: `WEBFLOW`\n33: \n34: **Expected references loaded** (exact relative paths under `.opencode/skills/sk-code/`):\n35: - `references/stack_detection.md`\n36: - `references/smart_routing.md`\n37: - `references/smart_routing.md`\n38: - `references/webflow/implementation/animation_workflows.md`\n39: - `references/webflow/javascript/quality_standards.md`\n40: - `references/webflow/verification/verification_workflows.md`\n41: - `references/motion_dev/performance_and_pitfalls.md`\n42: - `references/motion_dev/integration_patterns.md`\n43: \n44: **Expected assets loaded**:\n45: - `assets/webflow/checklists/code_quality_checklist.md`\n46: - `assets/webflow/checklists/verification_checklist.md`\n47: - `assets/motion_dev/snippets/hover_gesture.js`\n48: - `assets/motion_dev/snippets/in_view_reveal.js`\n49: \n50: **Expected agent dispatch**: none.\n51: \n52: **Pass/fail criteria with binary grading**:\n53: - **PASS** iff surface is `WEBFLOW`, `references/motion_dev/performance_and_pitfalls.md` loads, the user response cites Motion.dev reduced-motion guidance, and Webflow verification/a11y guidance is also loaded.\n54: - **FAIL** iff Motion.dev reduced-motion guidance is missing, Webflow guidance is missing, surface is not `WEBFLOW`, or an agent is dispatched.\n55: \n56: **Failure triage**:\n57: 1. If Motion reduced-motion guidance is missing, inspect `references/motion_dev/performance_and_pitfalls.md`.\n58: 2. If Webflow verification is missing, inspect `references/webflow/verification/verification_workflows.md`.\n59: 3. If the response only says \"disable animations\", check whether it preserves state changes and usability.\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: ## 3. TEST EXECUTION\n64: \n65: Run this scenario through the Phase 005 universal prompt using `SCENARIO_ID=CS-007`.\n66: \n67: Evidence files:\n68: - `/tmp/skc-CS-007-<cli>.txt`\n69: - `<spec-folder><cli>.yaml`\n70: \n71: ---\n72: \n73: ## 4. SOURCE FILES\n74: \n75: - `.opencode/skills/sk-code/references/motion_dev/performance_and_pitfalls.md` - Motion reduced-motion guidance.\n76: - `.opencode/skills/sk-code/references/webflow/implementation/animation_workflows.md` - Webflow animation accessibility guidance.\n77: - `.opencode/skills/sk-code/references/webflow/verification/verification_workflows.md` - Browser evidence expectations.\n78: - `.opencode/skills/sk-code/assets/motion_dev/snippets/hover_gesture.js` - Reduced-motion snippet pattern.\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: ## 5. SOURCE METADATA\n83: \n84: - **Created**: 2026-05-05\n85: - **Critical path**: No\n86: - **Destructive**: No\n87: - **Sandbox**: read-only routing analysis\n88: - **Concurrent-safe**: Yes\n89: - **Last validated**: pending Phase D matrix\n\n(End of file - total 89 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"CS-007: Prefers Reduced Motion Cross-Stack Guidance\"\ndescription: \"Verify Webflow plus Motion.dev accessibility prompts cite Motion.dev reduced-motion guidance and Webflow animation accessibility guidance.\"\n---\n\n# CS-007: Prefers Reduced Motion Cross-Stack Guidance\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThis scenario verifies accessibility guidance for Webflow Motion.dev work. The AI must load the Webflow animation/accessibility references and the Motion.dev reduced-motion guidance so it can cite both platform expectations and API-level caveats.\n\n---\n\n## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n\n**Realistic user prompt**:\n```text\nFor a Webflow page with motion.dev-powered cards in src/2_javascript/cards.js, how should sk-code route a prefers-reduced-motion fix before editing?\n```\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/07--cross-stack-routing/024-prefers-reduced-motion.md","time":{"start":1780373523638,"end":1780373523655}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b8cddaa3b01415f016a1e581385d481918ad78a18f5bab19d"}},"id":"prt_e86880cb1001BmaM1bS6fgIMOM","sessionID":"ses_1797a1220ffefMR5XwHZad3Rpm","messageID":"msg_e8687bcc4001cmmNK3o2tn488b"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780373523657,"sessionID":"ses_1797a1220ffefMR5XwHZad3Rpm","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_hny6tjMx78f3ul8BvpuKrhFG","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/07--cross-stack-routing/021-decision-matrix-routing.md","offset":1,"limit":80},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/07--cross-stack-routing/021-decision-matrix-routing.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"CS-004: Decision Matrix Routing\"\n3: description: \"Verify Motion.dev versus CSS hover-state questions load the motion_dev decision matrix instead of silently choosing a library.\"\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # CS-004: Decision Matrix Routing\n7: \n8: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n9: \n10: This scenario verifies that design-choice prompts load the decision matrix. The AI should name the trade-off between CSS, Motion.dev, GSAP, and WAAPI rather than silently defaulting to Motion.dev.\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n15: \n16: **Realistic user prompt**:\n17: ```text\n18: For a hover state on cards, should I use motion.dev or plain CSS? I need the routing decision and the references you would load, not an implementation.\n19: ```\n20: \n21: **Expected detection markers** (verbatim from `references/stack_detection.md`):\n22: ```text\n23: `motion_dev/` is a peer resource category rather than a surface. Surface detection still chooses WEBFLOW, OPENCODE, or UNKNOWN first; Motion.dev API, performance, and decision guidance is loaded afterward when the intent requires cross-stack animation context.\n24: ```\n25: \n26: **Expected surface**: `UNKNOWN` or `N/A`\n27: \n28: **Expected references loaded** (exact relative paths under `.opencode/skills/sk-code/`):\n29: - `references/stack_detection.md`\n30: - `references/smart_routing.md`\n31: - `references/smart_routing.md`\n32: - `references/motion_dev/decision_matrix.md`\n33: - `references/motion_dev/performance_and_pitfalls.md`\n34: - `references/motion_dev/integration_patterns.md`\n35: \n36: **Expected assets loaded**:\n37: - `assets/motion_dev/snippets/hover_gesture.js`\n38: \n39: **Expected agent dispatch**: none.\n40: \n41: **Pass/fail criteria with binary grading**:\n42: - **PASS** iff the AI lists `references/motion_dev/decision_matrix.md`, keeps surface as `UNKNOWN` or `N/A`, and its user response compares CSS and Motion.dev with conditions.\n43: - **FAIL** iff `decision_matrix.md` is omitted, the AI invents a surface, or it gives an implementation-only answer.\n44: \n45: **Failure triage**:\n46: 1. If no decision matrix loads, inspect `CODE_QUALITY / DECISION` in `references/smart_routing.md`.\n47: 2. If `WEBFLOW` is selected, verify the prompt contains no Webflow path, vendor global, or `wrangler.toml`.\n48: 3. If the response is one-sided, compare it against `references/motion_dev/decision_matrix.md`.\n49: \n50: ---\n51: \n52: ## 3. TEST EXECUTION\n53: \n54: Run this scenario through the Phase 005 universal prompt using `SCENARIO_ID=CS-004`. The expected answer may recommend CSS for simple hover and Motion.dev for timeline, gesture, or runtime-controlled cases, but the matrix must be loaded.\n55: \n56: Evidence files:\n57: - `/tmp/skc-CS-004-<cli>.txt`\n58: - `<spec-folder><cli>.yaml`\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ## 4. SOURCE FILES\n63: \n64: - `.opencode/skills/sk-code/references/motion_dev/decision_matrix.md` - Required decision reference.\n65: - `.opencode/skills/sk-code/references/motion_dev/performance_and_pitfalls.md` - Performance and reduced-motion caveats.\n66: - `.opencode/skills/sk-code/assets/motion_dev/snippets/hover_gesture.js` - Hover example when Motion.dev is justified.\n67: \n68: ---\n69: \n70: ## 5. SOURCE METADATA\n71: \n72: - **Created**: 2026-05-05\n73: - **Critical path**: No\n74: - **Destructive**: No\n75: - **Sandbox**: read-only routing analysis\n76: - **Concurrent-safe**: Yes\n77: - **Last validated**: pending Phase D matrix\n\n(End of file - total 77 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"CS-004: Decision Matrix Routing\"\ndescription: \"Verify Motion.dev versus CSS hover-state questions load the motion_dev decision matrix instead of silently choosing a library.\"\n---\n\n# CS-004: Decision Matrix Routing\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThis scenario verifies that design-choice prompts load the decision matrix. The AI should name the trade-off between CSS, Motion.dev, GSAP, and WAAPI rather than silently defaulting to Motion.dev.\n\n---\n\n## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n\n**Realistic user prompt**:\n```text\nFor a hover state on cards, should I use motion.dev or plain CSS? I need the routing decision and the references you would load, not an implementation.\n```\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/07--cross-stack-routing/021-decision-matrix-routing.md","time":{"start":1780373523643,"end":1780373523656}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b8cddaa3b01415f016a1e581385dc81919f8570132b9b13f3"}},"id":"prt_e86880cb7001DwQHPV5tadzdQi","sessionID":"ses_1797a1220ffefMR5XwHZad3Rpm","messageID":"msg_e8687bcc4001cmmNK3o2tn488b"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780373523662,"sessionID":"ses_1797a1220ffefMR5XwHZad3Rpm","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_FKyyP9atg6H1ROedMbAqO28y","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/07--cross-stack-routing/022-snippet-reuse-cross-stack.md","offset":1,"limit":80},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/07--cross-stack-routing/022-snippet-reuse-cross-stack.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"CS-005: Snippet Reuse Across Stacks\"\n3: description: \"Verify cross-stack Motion.dev snippet reuse surfaces the reusable snippet and flags the snake_case Webflow convention caveat.\"\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # CS-005: Snippet Reuse Across Stacks\n7: \n8: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n9: \n10: This scenario verifies that Motion.dev snippets can be reused outside Webflow while preserving naming-context honesty. The AI should surface the relevant snippet, explain what is reusable, and flag that some local examples use snake_case because Webflow guidance prefers that convention.\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n15: \n16: **Realistic user prompt**:\n17: ```text\n18: Can I reuse the sk-code Motion in-view reveal snippet in a non-Webflow vanilla JS page? Tell me which snippet and references you would load, and call out any naming-convention caveat.\n19: ```\n20: \n21: **Expected detection markers** (verbatim from `references/stack_detection.md`):\n22: ```text\n23: `motion_dev/` is a peer resource category rather than a surface. Surface detection still chooses WEBFLOW, OPENCODE, or UNKNOWN first; Motion.dev API, performance, and decision guidance is loaded afterward when the intent requires cross-stack animation context.\n24: ```\n25: \n26: **Expected surface**: `UNKNOWN` or `N/A`\n27: \n28: **Expected references loaded** (exact relative paths under `.opencode/skills/sk-code/`):\n29: - `references/stack_detection.md`\n30: - `references/smart_routing.md`\n31: - `references/motion_dev/quick_start.md`\n32: - `references/motion_dev/integration_patterns.md`\n33: - `references/motion_dev/scroll_and_gestures.md`\n34: - `references/webflow/javascript/style_guide.md`\n35: \n36: **Expected assets loaded**:\n37: - `assets/motion_dev/snippets/in_view_reveal.js`\n38: - `assets/motion_dev/snippets/animate_on_scroll.js`\n39: \n40: **Expected agent dispatch**: none.\n41: \n42: **Pass/fail criteria with binary grading**:\n43: - **PASS** iff the AI surfaces `assets/motion_dev/snippets/in_view_reveal.js`, states the snippet is cross-stack reusable with runtime adaptation, and explicitly flags the snake_case Webflow convention caveat.\n44: - **FAIL** iff the snippet is not named, Webflow is treated as required for reuse, or the naming caveat is missing.\n45: \n46: **Failure triage**:\n47: 1. If the snippet is missing, inspect `assets/motion_dev/snippets/`.\n48: 2. If the response says Webflow is required, re-read `references/smart_routing.md` Section 3.\n49: 3. If no caveat appears, inspect `references/webflow/javascript/style_guide.md` for local naming guidance.\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: ## 3. TEST EXECUTION\n54: \n55: Run this scenario through the Phase 005 universal prompt using `SCENARIO_ID=CS-005`. The grading checks the response content, not only the YAML path list.\n56: \n57: Evidence files:\n58: - `/tmp/skc-CS-005-<cli>.txt`\n59: - `<spec-folder><cli>.yaml`\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: ## 4. SOURCE FILES\n64: \n65: - `.opencode/skills/sk-code/assets/motion_dev/snippets/in_view_reveal.js` - Required reusable snippet.\n66: - `.opencode/skills/sk-code/references/motion_dev/integration_patterns.md` - Cross-stack integration guidance.\n67: - `.opencode/skills/sk-code/references/webflow/javascript/style_guide.md` - Snake_case caveat source.\n68: \n69: ---\n70: \n71: ## 5. SOURCE METADATA\n72: \n73: - **Created**: 2026-05-05\n74: - **Critical path**: No\n75: - **Destructive**: No\n76: - **Sandbox**: read-only routing analysis\n77: - **Concurrent-safe**: Yes\n78: - **Last validated**: pending Phase D matrix\n\n(End of file - total 78 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"CS-005: Snippet Reuse Across Stacks\"\ndescription: \"Verify cross-stack Motion.dev snippet reuse surfaces the reusable snippet and flags the snake_case Webflow convention caveat.\"\n---\n\n# CS-005: Snippet Reuse Across Stacks\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThis scenario verifies that Motion.dev snippets can be reused outside Webflow while preserving naming-context honesty. The AI should surface the relevant snippet, explain what is reusable, and flag that some local examples use snake_case because Webflow guidance prefers that convention.\n\n---\n\n## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n\n**Realistic user prompt**:\n```text\nCan I reuse the sk-code Motion in-view reveal snippet in a non-Webflow vanilla JS page? Tell me which snippet and references you would load, and call out any naming-convention caveat.\n```\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/07--cross-stack-routing/022-snippet-reuse-cross-stack.md","time":{"start":1780373523646,"end":1780373523661}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b8cddaa3b01415f016a1e581385e481918640eb60f37b7e1c"}},"id":"prt_e86880cbc001vIMhyDzZuJh8LX","sessionID":"ses_1797a1220ffefMR5XwHZad3Rpm","messageID":"msg_e8687bcc4001cmmNK3o2tn488b"}}
